  "response_text": "A single Energizer Max battery lies horizontally on a glossy, mirror-like surface in a silvery white studio space. The battery has black ends, a metallic grey body, a red-orange-yellow swoosh along the lower edge, and large white “Energizer” lettering with smaller yellow “MAX” text. Its reflection is visible beneath it, and the soft, pale background looks like shiny fabric or brushed metal.\n\nThe battery begins to subtly flex and bulge, as if something inside is pressing outward. A small silver shape pushes up through the top, then disappears and reappears at different points along the label. The surface ripples like soft metal. Gradually, a shiny chrome rabbit form emerges from the battery itself. First small limbs and rounded feet appear beneath it, then long upright ears rise above it. The figure looks like a liquid-metal version of the Energizer Bunny: smooth, reflective, silver, with tall rabbit ears and small arms holding tiny drumstick-like mallets.\n\nAs the bunny takes shape, the battery label bends and warps around its body, as though the bunny is inside the battery skin and pushing through it. The rabbit’s ears stretch upward, its arms extend out to the sides, and its feet plant on the reflective floor while the battery remains wrapped across its middle like a heavy cylindrical shell. The bunny poses with both mallets raised, then shifts its arms and head, continuing to move with a lively, springy posture.\n\nThe battery and bunny begin a playful acrobatic sequence. The battery tilts and rolls while the silver bunny clings to it, pops out of it, and seems to propel it. At moments the battery floats alone through the silvery space, rotating so its black end cap and metal terminal face forward. Then the bunny reappears beneath it, carrying or balancing the battery above its head. The bunny’s small body stretches upward under the weight, legs and feet extended in a dancer-like pose, while the battery stays prominent and readable with the Energizer branding wrapping around its side.\n\nThe battery continues to spin and glide across the reflective surface. The silver bunny repeatedly disappears into and emerges from the battery’s curved body, as if the rabbit is literally contained inside it. Sometimes only ears or small limbs are visible; at other times the whole rabbit rises from the top with both mallets lifted. The battery label remains the main visual anchor, with the large “Energizer” name and “MAX” text flashing into view as it rotates.\n\nNear the end, the battery settles back into a horizontal position. The chrome bunny rises from the top again, now clearly visible with long ears, rounded face, tiny arms, and mallets held up. It stands partly embedded in the battery’s middle, looking like it has burst through the Energizer label. The words “Do you have the Bunny inside?” appear in bold black text along the bottom of the screen. The bunny gestures with its mallets while the battery remains centered on the glossy surface.\n\nFinally, the bunny sinks back down into the battery, leaving the Energizer Max cell alone and intact in the center of the silver-white setting. The bottom text remains: “Do you have the Bunny inside?” The last image is a clean product view of the Energizer Max battery, reflected on the shiny surface.",
